Jannvi's Magical Adventure
Deep within an ancient forest, Jahnvi sets off on a magical journey, following a mysterious map that points the way to a hidden treasure. As she arrives at the end of her quest, a magical door emerges, displaying a special number that holds the key to the long-lost treasure
To open the door, Jahnvi needs to figure out the last digit of this magical number. Your job is to write a Java program to help Jahnvi uncover this secret digit

Input format:
The input is the integer that represents the magical number.

Output format:
The output is the integer that represents the last digit of the magical number.

Note: The code for handling inputs is already been given, your task is to fill in the required code.

Sample Test Cases
Test Case 1:
Expected Output:
2465
5

Test Case 2:
Expected Output:
201520
0

//solution
package 922255;
import java.util.Scanner;
public class EnchantedKey {
public static void main(String[] args) {
Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
int magicalNumber = scanner.nextInt();
int a = magicalNumber % 10;
System.out.println(a);
}
}
